Problem Statement
You are given an array containing N non-negative integers. Your task is to determine whether any value occurs more than once in the array.

If at least one duplicate element is present, print YES. Otherwise, print NO.

Input Format
The first line contains an integer T, denoting the number of test cases.

For each test case:
- The first line contains an integer N, representing the size of the array.
- The second line contains N space-separated integers.

Output Format
For each test case, print:
- YES if the array contains one or more duplicate values.
- NO if all elements in the array are distinct.

Constraints
1 ≤ T ≤ 50
1 ≤ N ≤ 10^5
0 ≤ arr[i] ≤ 10^5

Sample Testcase 0
Testcase Input
1
5
2 8 6 1 9
Testcase Output
NO
Explanation
Every element appears exactly once, so there are no duplicate values.

Sample Testcase 1
Testcase Input
1
6
4 7 1 9 4 3
Testcase Output
YES
Explanation
The value 4 appears twice in the array, so a duplicate exists.
